<paragraph id="8BC9368DFFC1FFDB09C99E5E495534ED" blockId="11.[151,1436,1374,1723]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">
The genus was revised by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE74B7CFFC1FFDB08E09E5E49B23721" author="Andersen" box="[446,649,1374,1399]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" refString="Andersen, N. M. (1982 b) Semiterrestrial water striders of the genera Eotrechus Kirkaldy and Chimarrhometra Bianchi (Insecta, Hemiptera, Gerridae). Steenstrupia, 9, 1 - 25." type="journal article" year="1982" yearSuffix="b">
Andersen (
<number id="3DBE24AAFFC1FFDB0B669E5E49493721" box="[568,626,1374,1399]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" value="1982.0">1982</number>
b)
</bibRefCitation>
and seven species were recognized. More recently, eight more species were described from 
<collectingCountry id="F361761DFFC1FFDB08D09E824AF137CD" box="[398,458,1410,1435]" name="India" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F361761DFFC1FFDB08879E82492437CD" box="[473,543,1410,1435]" name="China" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">China</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F361761DFFC1FFDB0B3E9E82498437CD" box="[608,703,1410,1435]" name="Vietnam" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE74B7CFFC1FFDB0B8E9E83489437CD" author="Tran" box="[720,943,1410,1435]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" refString="Tran, A. D. &amp; Yang, C. M. (2006) New species of the water strider genera Eotrechus Kirkaldy and Rhyacobates Esaki (Heteroptera: Gerridae) from Vietnam. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 54, 11 - 20." type="journal article" year="2006">
Tran &amp; Yang 
<number id="3DBE24AAFFC1FFDB0A2A9E82489437CD" box="[884,943,1410,1435]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE74B7CFFC1FFDB0AE09E834F9937CD" author="Tran" box="[958,1186,1410,1435]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" refString="Tran, A. D. &amp; Zettel, H. (2006) Notes on Eotrechus Kirkaldy, 1902 (Heteroptera: Gerridae), with descriptions of two new species. Zootaxa, 1353, 39 - 51." type="journal article" year="2006">
Tran &amp; Zettel 
<number id="3DBE24AAFFC1FFDB0D399E824F9937CD" box="[1127,1186,1410,1435]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE74B7CFFC1FFDB0DEF9E824BE937E9" author="Vitheepradit" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" refString="Vitheepradit, A. &amp; Sites, R. W. (2007) A review of Eotrechus Kirkaldy (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Gerridae) of Thailand with descriptions of three new species. Zootaxa, 1478, 1 - 19." type="journal article" year="2007">
Vitheepradit &amp; Sites 
<number id="3DBE24AAFFC1FFDB09C99EA74BE937E9" box="[151,210,1447,1471]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE74B7CFFC1FFDB09839EA64AF537E9" author="Polhemus" box="[221,462,1446,1471]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" refString="Polhemus, J. T., Tran, A. D. &amp; Polhemus, D. A. (2009) The genus Eotrechus (Heteroptera: Gerridae) in Vietnam, with descriptions of two new species. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 57, 29 - 37." type="journal article" year="2009">
Polhemus et al. 
<number id="3DBE24AAFFC1FFDB08CF9EA74AF537E9" box="[401,462,1447,1471]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This genus is distributed from 
<collectingCountry id="F361761DFFC1FFDB0A649EA6484F37E9" box="[826,884,1446,1471]" name="India" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">India</collectingCountry>
eastward to 
<collectingCountry id="F361761DFFC1FFDB0D5D9EA64F5937E9" box="[1027,1122,1446,1471]" name="Vietnam" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
and is found on the vertical rock faces of waterfalls. More specifically, members of this genus in 
<collectingCountry id="F361761DFFC1FFDB0A8E9ECA4F0F37B5" box="[976,1076,1482,1507]" name="Thailand" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">Thailand</collectingCountry>
seemed to occur closer to the margins of waterfalls, where the rocks were dampened by occasional splashing. Six species are known from 
<collectingCountry id="F361761DFFC1FFDB09C99D124BC6347D" box="[151,253,1554,1579]" name="Thailand" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, which is the most diverse fauna compared to that of other Southeast Asian countries. Most members of this genus in 
<collectingCountry id="F361761DFFC1FFDB08189D364A913419" box="[326,426,1590,1615]" name="Thailand" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">Thailand</collectingCountry>
are local endemics and restricted to certain mountains, with the exception of 
<taxonomicName id="4C764D0EFFC1FFDB0CDA9D374A093425" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Eotrechus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hygropetricus">
<emphasis id="B902EA9FFFC1FFDB0CDA9D374EAE3418" box="[1412,1429,1591,1614]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B902EA9FFFC1FFDB09C99D5A4A093425" box="[151,306,1626,1651]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">hygropetricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is found in several of the western mountain ranges (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE74B7CFFC1FFDB0A8A9D5A4E3B3425" author="Vitheepradit" box="[980,1280,1626,1651]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" refString="Vitheepradit, A. &amp; Sites, R. W. (2007) A review of Eotrechus Kirkaldy (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Gerridae) of Thailand with descriptions of three new species. Zootaxa, 1478, 1 - 19." type="journal article" year="2007">
Vitheepradit &amp; Sites 
<number id="3DBE24AAFFC1FFDB0D9D9D5B4E3B3425" box="[1219,1280,1627,1651]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Members of this genus were found only at elevations of 
<quantity id="4C8E9B68FFC1FFDB0BFD9D7E480E34C0" box="[675,821,1662,1687]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.74" metricValueMax="13.8" metricValueMin="5.68" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" unit="m" value="974.0" valueMax="1380.0" valueMin="568.0">568–1380 m</quantity>
and usually with 
<taxonomicName id="4C764D0EFFC1FFDB0D509D7E4E3834C1" box="[1038,1283,1662,1687]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Onychotrechus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="esakii">
<emphasis id="B902EA9FFFC1FFDB0D509D7E4E3834C1" box="[1038,1283,1662,1687]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">Onychotrechus esakii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on wet rock surfaces at waterfalls (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE74B7CFFC1FFDB08CC9DA2495934ED" author="Vitheepradit" box="[402,610,1698,1723]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" refString="Vitheepradit, A. (2008) The semiaquatic Heteroptera (Gerromorpha) of Thailand: Faunistics, Biogeography, and Phylogeography. Ph. D. Dissertation, University of Missouri, Columbia, Missouri, USA. [total page number not cited]" type="book" year="2008">
Vitheepradit 
<number id="3DBE24AAFFC1FFDB0B7B9DA3495934ED" box="[549,610,1699,1723]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
